v0.2<br>
<br>
Ok, I got interested in trying to uncover how SWG character stats interact and are used. I also wanted to have a thread where the stats information is brought together so that most questions are easily answered. Being an engineer IRL that meant that I have spent the last two nights making different characters, experimenting and taking lots of notes. The final regen formulas were the most tedious to find, and I hope people will help with the search for information on action costs (in a separate thread). <br>
<br>
The basics<br>
There are 9 basic character stats organized in three areas; health, action and mind. These stats areas appear to be completely independent of each other, linked only through character actions which affect more than one pool. Each group has three stat types that I call pool, cost, and regen. <br>
- Pool is the area amount available for use in a character action.<br>
- Cost governs how much a character action will cost for its pool.<br>
- Regen governs how quickly its pool regenerates itself.<br>
<br>
You set your character’s distribution of stats by deciding on a base species and then adding 4500 points into the different stats. The base species points can not be changed, and there are minimum and maximum points you can put into each stat. These limitations mean that there are only 1800 points (1800 = 4500-2700) available for you to place as you see fit. The adjustable 1800 stat points are originally set based on your character’s starting profession, but they can be immediately changed on the tutorial station, or slowly in the game via stat migration.<br>
<br>
My first version was a little unclear about the stat limits. Just add your species bonus(first table) to the profession default(second table) to get your starting stat. You can then use stat migration to get any value in the minimum to maximum range.<br>
FinalCharacterStat(minimum) = SpeciesBonus + Migration(min)<br>
FinalCharacterStat(maximum) = SpeciesBonus + Migration(max)<br>
<br>
<br>
